{
  "texts": [
    "In cases where we cannot decide whether an option has a property or not (such as movies that cannot be called 'funny', but we cannot say that they 'are not funny' either), binary logic should be replaced with multi-valued logic.",
    "And the rates in an N-soft set can be interpreted as the possible values of truth in an N-valued logic.",
    "Under this description, N-soft sets extend incomplete soft sets, which only admit one level of indeterminacy.",
    "Or as mentioned above, incomplete soft sets can be identified with 3-soft sets.",
    "Soft topology: first resultsTopology has become a renowned mathematical discipline whose origins are in the early 1900 s, when it was simply a part of set theory."
  ]
}